    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In geometry, a digons are polygons with two sides or edges and two vertices; pairs of vertices connected by two edges. A digon is degenerate in a Euclidean space, but may be non-degenerate in a spherical space.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
